The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Thursday, May 27, 2004 				 i-flex fourth quarter net at Rs 41 crore
 OUR BUREAUX																								May 26: i-flex Solutions Ltd has recorded a 26 per cent jump in net profits to Rs 41.13 crore for the fourth quarter ended March 31, 2004 compared with Rs 32.58 crore in the corresponding previous quarter.																								Income increased to Rs 172.19 crore during the reporting quarter against Rs 147.13 crore in the year-ago period.																								The company, however, reported a lower net profit at Rs 168.76 crore for the year ended March 2004 against Rs 173.96 crore in the previous fiscal. Income was higher at Rs 684.46 crore during the year from Rs 568.42 crore in 2002-03.																								The board has recommended a dividend of 70 per cent, which translates into Rs 3.50 per share.																								According to chairman and managing director Rajesh Hukku, Last year there has been a significant increase in our customer and country presence, alliance network and our own sales and marketing force. These reflect our readiness for the next phase of growth.																								The company said that it added 30 new customers during the reporting quarter, including 17 customers through the acquisition of SuperSolutions Corporation, taking the total customers base to 480, up from 450 in the corresponding previous quarter. Thermax net up 13%																								Thermax Ltd has posted a 12.85 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 62.86 crore on a consolidated basis for the year ended March 31, 2004 compared with Rs 55.7 crore posted in the previous fiscal. 																								The board has recommended a 120 per cent dividend for 2003-04, and also a dividend on 6 per cent redeemable preference shares on a pro-rata basis for a period of 192 days from September 22, 2003 to March 31, 2004, Thermax informed the Bombay Stock Exchange today. Total income rose to Rs 829.35 crore during the year, from Rs 741.06 crore posted in the previous year.																								On a standalone basis, the company has posted a net profit of 54.09 crore for the year compared with Rs 48.24 crore posted a year ago. Total income rose to Rs 603.81 crore (Rs 552.53 crore). Tata Honeywell dividend 																								Tata Honeywell today reported a 50.5 per cent jump in net profit at Rs 25.3 crore for 2003-04 against Rs 16.8 crore reported in the preceding fiscal. The company has declared an 80 per cent dividend for the shareholders.																								Revenues increased by 27.2 per cent to Rs 342.4 crore (Rs 269.1 crore).Crompton Greaves																								Crompton Greaves Ltd today reported a 152 per cent jump in net profit at Rs 70.83 crore for 2003-04 against Rs 28.1 crore posted a year earlier. The board has announced a dividend of Rs 4 per share. 																								Total income rose to Rs 1,738.3 crore (Rs 1,600.4 crore).Clariant bottomline rises 																								Clariant (India) Ltd has posted a 6.5 per cent growth in net profit at Rs 20.85 crore for the year ended March 31, 2004 compared with Rs 19.58 crore in the previous year. The board has recommended a final dividend of Rs 6 per share, which together with the interim dividend of Rs 5 already paid in November last year, makes a total of Rs 11 against Rs 10 announced last year.
